Acme Slides

These are a series of shell scripts written to do text-based slide shows on the Acme text editor.  This application was inspired by the slide show scripts that Russ Cox wrote in his tour of Acme

Format of slides
Slides have the .slide file extension and file names are numbers going from one up.

Scripts
sts: Starts a slide show in the current directory if it contain slide files.

slide+: Goes to the next slide.

slide-: Goes to the previous slide.

sn: Gives the slide number.  For internal use by the other scripts

slide: Outputs a slide into the current window.  For internal use by slide+ and slide-
